description.narrative: Southwestern;Haiti is particularly vulnerable to natural disasters. On 14 August, a 7.2-magnitude earthquake hit that region severely which left more than 2,200 dead and 12,000 injured. UNICEF focused its interventions on providing inclusive, accessible, safe and appropriate mental health and psychosocial support and;case management to unaccompanied or separated children including vulnerable family, the strengthening child protection community-based structures, the prevention of gender-based violence via sensitization and services provision for survivors. UNICEF also provided support to civil society organizations to protect families and children, particularly for those who are expelled and deported returning to West and North departments;and across the border. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/01/2022
